<DocsLayout title="Roadmap" description="Product roadmap for the sens.legal ecosystem.">
  <h1>Roadmap</h1>

  <p>
    All projects are currently in <strong>alpha</strong>. This roadmap reflects
    planned work based on open issues across the three repositories.
  </p>

  <h2>Valter</h2>

  <h4>Near-term</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Demo/sandbox environment for public testing</li>
    <li>API documentation improvements</li>
    <li>Rate limiting and API key management</li>
    <li>Performance optimization for graph queries</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Medium-term</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Expanded knowledge graph with temporal evolution tracking</li>
    <li>Multi-court support (TJs, TST)</li>
    <li>Real-time ingestion pipeline</li>
    <li>Enhanced MCP tools with streaming responses</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Juca</h2>

  <h4>Near-term</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>User authentication and session management</li>
    <li>Briefing workflow polish</li>
    <li>Canvas improvements</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Medium-term</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Multi-tenant support</li>
    <li>Case management dashboard</li>
    <li>Document annotation and collaboration</li>
    <li>Mobile-responsive interface</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Leci</h2>

  <h4>Near-term</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Define backend architecture</li>
    <li>Brazilian legislation data model</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Medium-term</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Legislation ingestion pipeline</li>
    <li>Integration with Valter's knowledge graph</li>
    <li>MCP tools for legislation access</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Ecosystem</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Cross-project search from the portal</li>
    <li>Unified authentication across projects</li>
    <li>Public API keys for testing</li>
    <li>Comprehensive developer documentation</li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>
